Service Engineer – Flow (SVC-Flow/201402/01/SG)
Job ID
EPM-00006592
Country
Singapore
State/Province
Singapore
City
Singapore
Publish Start Date
Feb 4 2014
Job Level
Experienced (Non-Manager)
|
Responsibilities:
Plan, schedule, conduct and coordinate program of assigned Instrument calibration/troubleshooting work and projects either Singapore or Overseas.
Analyze customer issues, process, reports, P&I drawings, tests and other data to plan service work for faster solution.
Ensure proper interdisciplinary coordination and effective communication on service projects/contracts and related activities.
Provide telephone technical support and recommendations to customer for instrument related issues and attend to Factory Acceptance Test for onshore and offshore customers.
Write accurate professional reports and update company’s CRM system on the job progress.
Ensure all in-filed activities are carried out safely complying with company Environmental Health and Safety (EHS) guidelines and procedures.
Requirements:
Degree or Diploma in Instrument/Electronics Engineering with 2 to 5 years of related experience in the instrumentation and controls field, particularly in FLOW instruments.
Ability to be a team player with strong problem solving skills to accomplish tasks.
Fast learner with strong interpersonal skills and positive work attitude.
Able to travel on short notice and help customer service process orders, if needed.
Possess a Class 3 driving license would be preferred.